# F7 Controller — local-dev environment template.
#
# Real deployments: install.sh / install.ps1 generate a strong POSTGRES_PASSWORD
# and write a .env automatically — you do NOT need this file.
#
# Local dev only: `cp .env.example .env` before `docker compose up`. The compose
# file requires POSTGRES_PASSWORD and FSEVEN_APP_DB_PASSWORD with no default
# (fails closed if unset, PB7/PB8), so these throwaway values keep a from-scratch
# `docker compose` run working.

# REQUIRED — Postgres owner credential, used by DATABASE_ADMIN_URL + OpenFGA
# datastore (no default in compose).
POSTGRES_PASSWORD=devpassword

# REQUIRED — password for the least-privilege fseven_app DB role the controller
# serving pool connects as after the CD10 RLS serving-role cutover (no default in
# compose; PB8). Real deployments: install.sh / install.ps1 generate a strong one.
FSEVEN_APP_DB_PASSWORD=devapppassword

# Optional — published controller image tag (defaults to :latest).
# CONTROLLER_IMAGE=ghcr.io/f7-platform/public-agent-binaries/controller:latest
